<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Parachute — NVC Pitch Deck</title>
    <meta name="robots" content="noindex">
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Instrument+Serif:ital@0;1&family=DM+Sans:ital,opsz,wght@0,9..40,300;0,9..40,400;0,9..40,500;1,9..40,400&family=JetBrains+Mono:wght@400&display=swap">
    <style>
        :root {
            --bg:           #faf8f4;
            --bg-soft:      #f3f0ea;
            --fg:           #2c2a26;
            --fg-muted:     #6b6860;
            --fg-dim:       #9a9690;
            --accent:       #4a7c59;
            --accent-soft:  rgba(74, 124, 89, 0.08);
            --border:       #e4e0d8;
            --serif: 'Instrument Serif', Georgia, serif;
            --sans:  'DM Sans', system-ui, sans-serif;
            --mono:  'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
        }

        *, *::before, *::after { margin: 0; padding: 0; box-sizing: border-box; }
        html { scroll-behavior: smooth; scroll-snap-type: y mandatory; }

        body {
            background: var(--bg);
            font-family: var(--sans);
            color: var(--fg);
            -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;
            line-height: 1.6;
        }

        .slide {
            min-height: 100vh;
            display: flex;
            flex-direction: column;
            justify-content: center;
            padding: 4rem 6rem;
            border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
            scroll-snap-align: start;
            position: relative;
        }
        .slide:last-child { border-bottom: none; }

        .slide-label {
            font-size: 0.65rem;
            letter-spacing: 0.14em;
            text-transform: uppercase;
            color: var(--accent);
            font-weight: 500;
            margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
        }

        .slide-headline {
            font-family: var(--serif);
            font-size: clamp(2.8rem, 5.5vw, 4.5rem);
            font-weight: 400;
            letter-spacing: -0.02em;
            line-height: 1.08;
            color: var(--fg);
            margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
        }
        .slide-headline em { font-style: italic; color: var(--fg-muted); }

        .slide-sub {
            font-size: 1.2rem;
            color: var(--fg-muted);
            max-width: 600px;
            line-height: 1.6;
        }
        .slide-sub strong { color: var(--fg); font-weight: 500; }

        /* -- Speaker notes -- */
        .speaker-notes {
            display: none;
            margin-top: 2rem;
            padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;
            background: var(--bg-soft);
            border: 1px solid var(--border);
            border-radius: 8px;
            max-width: 700px;
            font-size: 0.85rem;
            color: var(--fg-muted);
            line-height: 1.7;
        }
        .speaker-notes .notes-label {
            font-size: 0.6rem;
            letter-spacing: 0.12em;
            text-transform: uppercase;
            color: var(--accent);
            font-weight: 500;
            margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
        }
        body.show-notes .speaker-notes { display: block; }

        .notes-toggle {
            position: fixed;
            bottom: 1.5rem;
            right: 1.5rem;
            z-index: 100;
            padding: 0.5rem 1rem;
            background: var(--fg);
            color: var(--bg);
            border: none;
            border-radius: 6px;
            font-family: var(--sans);
            font-size: 0.75rem;
            font-weight: 500;
            cursor: pointer;
            opacity: 0.7;
            transition: opacity 0.15s;
        }
        .notes-toggle:hover { opacity: 1; }

        /* -- Stat row -- */
        .stat-row {
            display: flex;
            gap: 0;
            margin: 1.5rem 0;
            border: 1px solid var(--border);
            border-radius: 10px;
            overflow: hidden;
            background: #fff;
            max-width: 500px;
        }
        .stat {
            flex: 1;
            padding: 1.5rem;
            border-right: 1px solid var(--border);
            text-align: center;
        }
        .stat:last-child { border-right: none; }
        .stat-num {
            font-family: var(--serif);
            font-size: 2.5rem;
            color: var(--accent);
            line-height: 1;
            letter-spacing: -0.03em;
            margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
        }
        .stat-label {
            font-size: 0.75rem;
            color: var(--fg-muted);
            line-height: 1.4;
        }

        /* -- Flywheel -- */
        .flywheel {
            display: flex;
            flex-direction: column;
            max-width: 500px;
            margin: 1rem 0;
        }
        .fw-step {
            font-family: var(--serif);
            font-size: 1.35rem;
            color: var(--fg);
            padding: 0.85rem 0;
            border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
            gap: 0.75rem;
        }
        .fw-step:first-child { border-top: 1px solid var(--border); }
        .fw-step.final { color: var(--accent); }
        .fw-num {
            font-family: var(--mono);
            font-size: 0.65rem;
            color: var(--fg-dim);
            letter-spacing: 0.06em;
            flex-shrink: 0;
            width: 1.5rem;
        }

        /* -- Tier table -- */
        .tier-table {
            margin: 1rem 0;
            border: 1px solid var(--border);
            border-radius: 10px;
            overflow: hidden;
            background: #fff;
            max-width: 500px;
        }
        .tier-row {
            display: flex;
            align-items: baseline;
            gap: 1.25rem;
            padding: 0.6rem 1.25rem;
            border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
        }
        .tier-row:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
        .tier-price {
            font-family: var(--serif);
            font-size: 1.3rem;
            color: var(--accent);
            min-width: 4.5rem;
            flex-shrink: 0;
        }
        .tier-price span { font-family: var(--sans); font-size: 0.7rem; color: var(--fg-dim); }
        .tier-body { font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--fg-muted); }
        .tier-body strong { color: var(--fg); font-weight: 500; }
        .tier-highlight { background: var(--accent-soft); }

        /* -- Financial table -- */
        .fin-table {
            margin: 1rem 0;
            border: 1px solid var(--border);
            border-radius: 10px;
            overflow: hidden;
            background: #fff;
            max-width: 600px;
        }
        .fin-table table {
            width: 100%;
            border-collapse: collapse;
        }
        .fin-table th {
            font-size: 0.65rem;
            letter-spacing: 0.06em;
            text-transform: uppercase;
            color: var(--fg-dim);
            font-weight: 500;
            text-align: center;
            padding: 0.6rem 0.75rem;
            border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
            background: var(--bg-soft);
        }
        .fin-table th:first-child { text-align: left; }
        .fin-table td {
            font-size: 0.85rem;
            color: var(--fg-muted);
            padding: 0.5rem 0.75rem;
            border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
            text-align: center;
        }
        .fin-table td:first-child {
            font-weight: 500;
            color: var(--fg);
            text-align: left;
            font-size: 0.8rem;
        }
        .fin-table tr:last-child td { border-bottom: none; }
        .fin-table .highlight { color: var(--accent); font-weight: 500; }

        /* -- Ask box -- */
        .ask-box {
            border: 1px solid var(--border);
            border-radius: 10px;
            overflow: hidden;
            background: #fff;
            margin: 1rem 0;
            max-width: 500px;
        }
        .ask-row {
            display: flex;
            justify-content: space-between;
            align-items: baseline;
            padding: 0.9rem 1.25rem;
            border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
        }
        .ask-row:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
        .ask-row .lbl { font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--fg-muted); }
        .ask-row .val { font-family: var(--serif); font-size: 1.1rem; color: var(--fg); }

        .close-quote {
            font-family: var(--serif);
            font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 3vw, 2rem);
            color: var(--fg);
            margin-top: 2.5rem;
            line-height: 1.3;
            max-width: 550px;
        }
        .close-links {
            margin-top: 1.5rem;
            font-size: 0.85rem;
            color: var(--fg-dim);
        }
        .close-links a { color: var(--accent); text-decoration: none; }
        .close-links a:hover { text-decoration: underline; }

        /* -- Architecture diagram -- */
        .arch-diagram {
            margin: 1rem 0;
            border: 1px solid var(--border);
            border-radius: 10px;
            overflow: hidden;
            background: #fff;
            max-width: 650px;
            padding: 1.5rem 2rem;
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
            justify-content: center;
            gap: 0;
        }
        .arch-spoke { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.5rem; }
        .arch-spoke-label {
            font-family: var(--mono);
            font-size: 0.6rem;
            letter-spacing: 0.1em;
            text-transform: uppercase;
            color: var(--fg-dim);
            margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
        }
        .arch-spoke.right { align-items: flex-end; }
        .arch-spoke.right .arch-spoke-label { text-align: right; }
        .arch-box {
            border: 1px solid var(--border);
            border-radius: 6px;
            padding: 0.4rem 0.9rem;
            font-size: 0.8rem;
            color: var(--fg);
            background: var(--bg);
            white-space: nowrap;
        }
        .arch-hub {
            border: 2px solid var(--accent);
            background: var(--accent-soft);
            color: var(--accent);
            font-weight: 500;
            border-radius: 10px;
            padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
            text-align: center;
            font-size: 0.85rem;
            line-height: 1.5;
            flex-shrink: 0;
            margin: 0 0.25rem;
        }
        .arch-hub strong { display: block; font-size: 0.95rem; }
        .arch-connector {
            font-family: var(--mono);
            font-size: 0.75rem;
            color: var(--fg-dim);
            padding: 0 0.5rem;
            flex-shrink: 0;
            display: flex;
            flex-direction: column;
            align-items: center;
            gap: 0.15rem;
        }
        .arch-connector .conn-label {
            font-size: 0.55rem;
            letter-spacing: 0.06em;
            text-transform: uppercase;
        }

        /* -- Competitor landscape -- */
        .landscape {
            display: grid;
            grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
            gap: 0;
            max-width: 600px;
            margin: 1rem 0;
            border: 1px solid var(--border);
            border-radius: 10px;
            overflow: hidden;
            background: #fff;
        }
        .landscape-quadrant {
            padding: 1.25rem;
            border-right: 1px solid var(--border);
            border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
        }
        .landscape-quadrant:nth-child(2n) { border-right: none; }
        .landscape-quadrant:nth-child(n+3) { border-bottom: none; }
        .landscape-quadrant .quad-label {
            font-size: 0.55rem;
            letter-spacing: 0.12em;
            text-transform: uppercase;
            color: var(--fg-dim);
            font-weight: 500;
            margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
        }
        .landscape-quadrant .quad-names {
            font-family: var(--serif);
            font-size: 1.05rem;
            color: var(--fg-muted);
            line-height: 1.7;
        }
        .landscape-quadrant.ours { background: var(--accent-soft); }
        .landscape-quadrant.ours .quad-label { color: var(--accent); }
        .landscape-quadrant.ours .quad-names { color: var(--accent); font-weight: 500; }

        /* -- Persona cards -- */
        .persona-row {
            display: flex;
            gap: 1.5rem;
            margin: 1rem 0;
            max-width: 900px;
        }
        .persona-card {
            flex: 1;
            border: 1px solid var(--border);
            border-radius: 10px;
            padding: 1.5rem;
            background: #fff;
        }
        .persona-card .persona-who {
            font-family: var(--serif);
            font-size: 1.15rem;
            color: var(--fg);
            margin-bottom: 0.35rem;
        }
        .persona-card .persona-how {
            font-size: 0.85rem;
            color: var(--fg-muted);
            line-height: 1.5;
        }

        /* -- Mobile -- */
        @media (max-width: 768px) {
            .slide { padding: 3rem 1.5rem; }
            .stat-row { flex-direction: column; }
            .stat { border-right: none; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); }
            .stat:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
            .landscape { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
            .landscape-quadrant { border-right: none !important; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border) !important; }
            .landscape-quadrant:last-child { border-bottom: none !important; }
            .persona-row { flex-direction: column; }
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

    <!-- Download bar -->
    <div style="position: fixed; top: 0; left: 0; right: 0; z-index: 100; background: var(--bg); border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 0.75rem 2rem; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: space-between;">
        <span style="font-family: var(--serif); font-size: 0.95rem; color: var(--fg);">Parachute &mdash; NVC Pitch Deck</span>
        <div style="display: flex; gap: 0.75rem;">
            <a href="/nvc/ES_Parachute.pdf" download style="padding: 0.35rem 0.75rem; background: var(--accent); color: #fff; border-radius: 5px; text-decoration: none; font-size: 0.75rem; font-weight: 500;">Executive Summary (PDF)</a>
            <a href="/nvc/Parachute.pptx" download style="padding: 0.35rem 0.75rem; background: var(--accent); color: #fff; border-radius: 5px; text-decoration: none; font-size: 0.75rem; font-weight: 500;">Pitch Deck (PPTX)</a>
            <a href="/nvc/" style="padding: 0.35rem 0.75rem; background: var(--bg-soft); color: var(--fg); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 5px; text-decoration: none; font-size: 0.75rem; font-weight: 500;">Full Summary</a>
        </div>
    </div>

    <button class="notes-toggle" onclick="document.body.classList.toggle('show-notes'); this.textContent = document.body.classList.contains('show-notes') ? 'Hide Notes' : 'Speaker Notes';">Speaker Notes</button>

    <!-- ============================================ -->
    <!-- SLIDE 1 — ASPIRATION                        -->
    <!-- ============================================ -->
    <section class="slide" style="padding-top: 6rem;">
        <div style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 4rem;">
            <div style="flex: 1;">
                <div class="slide-label">Parachute</div>
                <h2 class="slide-headline">Capture. Connect.<br>Compound.</h2>
                <p class="slide-sub">A knowledge layer that makes any AI truly yours.</p>
            </div>
            <div style="flex: 0 0 auto;">
                <img src="/nvc/images/pendant-worn.png" alt="Person wearing Parachute pendant outdoors" style="width: 340px; border-radius: 12px; box-shadow: 0 4px 24px rgba(0,0,0,0.08);">
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="speaker-notes">
            <div class="notes-label">Speaker Notes</div>
            A thought on a walk. A note after a meeting. An idea at 2am. Right now, those are scattered &mdash; lost in apps that don't talk to each other and invisible to the AI tools we rely on. Parachute captures your thinking wherever you are, connects it into a structured knowledge graph, and compounds it over time into something that makes every AI you use more personal, more capable, more yours. I'm wearing one of our capture devices right now. This is Parachute.
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ============================================ -->
    <!-- SLIDE 2 — THE RACE                          -->
    <!-- ============================================ -->
    <section class="slide">
        <div class="slide-label">The Landscape</div>
        <h2 class="slide-headline">Everyone is building<br>AI agents.</h2>
        <p class="slide-sub">OpenClaw. Claude Cowork. Perplexity Computer. Manus.<br>We were too. Features get cloned in weeks. <strong>So we stopped trying to win that race.</strong></p>
        <div class="speaker-notes">
            <div class="notes-label">Speaker Notes</div>
            OpenClaw. Claude Cowork. Perplexity Computer. Manus. There are dozens of companies racing to build the best AI agent. Over 100 million people already pay $20+/month for AI. We started here too &mdash; we were building an agentic computing platform, a full AI-powered operating system. But we watched features get cloned in weeks. Every new capability one platform shipped, three others had within a month. It's a race to the bottom, and the big labs have billions of dollars to outspend everyone. Some startups in this space get acquired &mdash; Liminary, backed by Madrona, is doing something adjacent. But they're building within the agent race. We stopped trying to win that race. We asked: what's actually missing? What do all of these agents need that none of them are building?
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ============================================ -->
    <!-- SLIDE 3 — THE PROBLEM                       -->
    <!-- ============================================ -->
    <section class="slide">
        <div class="slide-label">The Problem</div>
        <h2 class="slide-headline">There&rsquo;s no<br>knowledge layer.</h2>
        <p class="slide-sub">Every AI stores your context as <strong>one flat text file.</strong><br>And to give it context, you have to talk to it. There&rsquo;s no way to just <em>think</em> and have it become context.</p>
        <div class="speaker-notes">
            <div class="notes-label">Speaker Notes</div>
            Every AI platform &mdash; ChatGPT, Claude, Gemini &mdash; stores your personal context the same way: one big text file. It remembers your name, maybe a few preferences. It doesn't know six months of your thinking. And to give it context, you have to talk to it directly. There's no way to just think for yourself &mdash; on a walk, in the car &mdash; and have that become context your AI can use. You might ask, "why not just dictate into ChatGPT?" Because then your thoughts are trapped inside one platform, unstructured, unsearchable, and gone the moment you switch tools. The knowledge layer between you and your AI doesn't exist. We're building it.
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ============================================ -->
    <!-- SLIDE 4 — THE PRODUCT                       -->
    <!-- ============================================ -->
    <section class="slide">
        <div style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 3rem;">
            <div style="flex: 1;">
                <div class="slide-label">The Product</div>
                <h2 class="slide-headline">Parachute Daily.</h2>
                <p class="slide-sub">Voice-first journal. Talk or type. Phone, web, or pendant.<br>
                <span style="font-size: 0.9rem;">Open source &middot; Local-first &middot; Your data is yours.</span></p>
            </div>
            <div style="flex: 0 0 auto; display: flex; gap: 1.5rem; align-items: flex-end;">
                <img src="/nvc/images/daily-capture.png" alt="Parachute Daily capture view" style="width: 200px; border-radius: 12px; box-shadow: 0 4px 24px rgba(0,0,0,0.08);">
                <img src="/nvc/images/daily-reader.png" alt="Parachute Daily reader view" style="width: 200px; border-radius: 12px; box-shadow: 0 4px 24px rgba(0,0,0,0.08);">

                <div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; align-items: center; gap: 0.5rem;">
                    <img src="/nvc/images/pendant-render.png" alt="Parachute pendant" style="width: 100px; border-radius: 8px; box-shadow: 0 2px 12px rgba(0,0,0,0.06);">
                    <span style="font-size: 0.65rem; color: var(--fg-dim);">Pendant</span>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="speaker-notes">
            <div class="notes-label">Speaker Notes</div>
            Parachute Daily is a voice-first journal. Talk or type &mdash; on your phone, on the web, or through a wearable pendant. Your words get transcribed and structured into a personal knowledge graph: notes, tags, and links. Simple for humans, native for AI. Most people will start with the app on their phone. The pendant is an accessory for people who want frictionless voice capture &mdash; press a button, talk on a walk, your thoughts are structured by the time you're home. Working prototype, on stage today. On privacy: this is a Public Benefit Corporation. The code is open source. Your data is local-first &mdash; it lives on your device by default. The cloud is opt-in, and if you choose it, we use end-to-end encryption. You can export everything, self-host, or leave at any time. We designed this for trust from day one, not as an afterthought.
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ============================================ -->
    <!-- SLIDE 5 — HOW IT WORKS                      -->
    <!-- ============================================ -->
    <section class="slide">
        <div class="slide-label">How It Works</div>
        <h2 class="slide-headline">Spin up a vault.<br>Give any AI a link.</h2>
        <p class="slide-sub" style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">Built on <strong>MCP</strong> &mdash; the open standard for connecting AI to tools.<br>Your data stays yours. Works with every AI, not instead of one.</p>
        <div class="arch-diagram">
            <div class="arch-spoke">
                <div class="arch-spoke-label">you</div>
                <span class="arch-box">Parachute Daily</span>
                <span class="arch-box">Pendant</span>
                <span class="arch-box">Phone &middot; Web</span>
            </div>
            <div class="arch-connector">&harr;</div>
            <div class="arch-hub">
                <strong>Parachute Vault</strong>
                Notes &middot; Tags &middot; Links
            </div>
            <div class="arch-connector">
                &harr;
                <span class="conn-label">MCP</span>
            </div>
            <div class="arch-spoke right">
                <div class="arch-spoke-label">your AI</div>
                <span class="arch-box">Claude</span>
                <span class="arch-box">ChatGPT</span>
                <span class="arch-box">Gemini</span>
                <span class="arch-box">Any agent</span>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="speaker-notes">
            <div class="notes-label">Speaker Notes</div>
            Your data lives in a Parachute Vault &mdash; a personal knowledge graph organized around notes, tags, and links. It's accessible to any AI via MCP, the open standard Anthropic created for connecting AI to tools. You spin up a vault in seconds and give any AI a link. That's the whole setup. Whatever AI you already use &mdash; Claude, ChatGPT, Gemini &mdash; Parachute makes it better. You don't switch anything. You add Parachute. This is how we stay independent from any one LLM. We're not tied to a single model. We speak an open protocol that any AI can use. As users settle into different AI camps, we're the layer that works across all of them. That's why we're not in the race to the bottom on AI features &mdash; we're building the infrastructure underneath it.
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ============================================ -->
    <!-- SLIDE 6 — COMPETITIVE LANDSCAPE              -->
    <!-- ============================================ -->
    <section class="slide">
        <div class="slide-label">Competitive Landscape</div>
        <h2 class="slide-headline">The magic exists.<br>It&rsquo;s not accessible.</h2>
        <div style="display: flex; gap: 2.5rem; align-items: flex-start; margin-top: 0.5rem;">
            <div class="landscape" style="max-width: 500px; flex-shrink: 0;">
                <div class="landscape-quadrant">
                    <div class="quad-label">Note apps</div>
                    <div class="quad-names">Obsidian<br>Apple Notes<br>Notion</div>
                </div>
                <div class="landscape-quadrant">
                    <div class="quad-label">AI platforms</div>
                    <div class="quad-names">ChatGPT<br>Gemini<br>Claude</div>
                </div>
                <div class="landscape-quadrant" style="grid-column: span 2; border-right: none; border-bottom: none;">
                    <div class="quad-label" style="color: var(--accent);">Parachute &mdash; accessible to everyone</div>
                    <div class="quad-names" style="color: var(--accent); font-weight: 500;">Open &middot; Portable &middot; Agent-native</div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div style="flex: 0 0 auto;">
                <img src="/nvc/images/obsidian-claude-screenshot.jpg" alt="Obsidian + Claude Code workflow" style="width: 380px; border-radius: 10px; box-shadow: 0 4px 24px rgba(0,0,0,0.1); border: 1px solid var(--border);">
