            Here's what convinced us this is the right thing to build. Obsidian is a note-taking app &mdash; 8 people, bootstrapped, profitable, over a million users. And a growing community of power users are connecting Obsidian to Claude Code and other AI tools. Give an AI a structured knowledge base and it can work magic. But it requires markdown files, plugin configuration, command-line tools, and file system access. It's incredible for developers and power users. But 99% of people will never do that. On the other side, Apple Notes and Notion have hundreds of millions of users but no AI integration beyond basic features. And the AI platforms themselves &mdash; ChatGPT, Gemini, Claude &mdash; are smart but siloed. Your data is trapped inside their ecosystem. Parachute takes the magic of Obsidian + AI and makes it accessible to everyone. No file system, no CLI, no plugins. Just a vault you spin up in seconds with a link any AI can use. The PKM market is $2.5 billion and growing 16% annually. Obsidian proved the model works with a tiny team. We're building the version that scales to the other 99%.
